    <title>[Font] Dyslexic Mode</title>
    <link>https://fol-archive.netlify.app/t/font-dyslexic-mode/54092</link>
    <description>Similar to &quot;colorblind mode&quot; that other games offer, I propose adding something I&#39;d affectionately call &quot;Dyslexic Mode&quot;, whereby people could click a button to change **all** displayed text from its usual typeface into a dyslexic-friendly version.

The open-source version of this font is called [Open Dyslexic](https://www.opendyslexic.org/), if you&#39;re interested.

Since Throne of Lies has _a lot_ of text, I think this could be a really good option, though I have no idea how hard it would be to implement. I don&#39;t personally struggle with dyslexia, but I know my husband, who does, would be much better equipped to keep up with the flow of the game if there were a dyslexic font option.

After all, colorblind mode is meant to help with visually-heavy games. It makes sense that there should be a similar option for text-heavy games as well.

Thoughts?</description>
    
